The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 27 September is 373,719 (664 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 September, there were 31,041 new confirmed cases (55.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 September, there were 19,489 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 59% (11552 extra cases).
